I20040219
This bug appears to be precluding me from opening the PDE Manifest editor.
The only way I can get toolbar actions to show is to continually reset my 
perspectives. I cannot get the manifest editor to open no matter what I try. 
Any workarounds?

This appears to be special to the Java perspective. I have much more success 
opening editors in the debug perspective.

This was a problem that was introduced between I20040218 and I20040219.  I did 
not realize there was going to be another build submission, and so partial 
work of mine ended up in I20040219. 
 
Brief synopsis: I now disallow duplicate identifiers in cool bars, and provide 
generic support for any implementation of ContributionManager to reject 
particular items.  At start-up, duplicate items are inserted into the cool bar 
(a minimum set is inserted, and then the old state is restored).  This led to 
a strange situation where some items were rejected due to duplication, but the 
old items were blown away by a subsequent "setLayout()" call. 
 
Let me know if this problem recurs in any build >= N20040220.
